The paper deals with universal compression, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the analysis of randomized algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of Poisson-sampling technique and the derivation of a single-letter formula suggest that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG), as well as computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
